<collectingCountry box="[1285,1373,750,774]" name="Finland" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Finland</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry name="Germany" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Germany</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[225,375,786,810]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Great Britain</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[386,438,786,810]" name="Italy" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Italy</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[497,634,786,810]" name="Switzerland" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Switzerland</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="key">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,714,1028]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,386,823,847]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Key characters.</emphasis>
Paired patches on abdominal terga 
<number box="[789,831,822,846]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="4.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="2.0">2–6</number>
(
<number box="[848,863,822,846]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="7.0">7</number>
) unpigmented; tegulae, posterior margin of pronotum, and metatibia mostly black. Ratio of flagellum length to head breadth in females 
<number box="[1141,1227,858,882]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1.85" valueMax="2.1" valueMin="1.6">1.6–2.1</number>
, in males 
<number box="[1345,1432,858,882]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="3.1" valueMax="3.5" valueMin="2.7">2.7–3.5</number>
, and eye length to head length 
<number box="[489,576,894,918]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1.4" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.3">1.3–1.5</number>
. Number of serrulae 
<number box="[813,843,894,918]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="14.0">14</number>
, conspicuously papilliform (
<figureCitation box="[1165,1250,894,918]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 39" captionStartId="26.[151,264,1927,1950]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,193,1906]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 39. Lancets (valvulae 1) / lancet (valvula 1) and lance (valvula 2) of Empria longicornis group: 36, E. alpina, lancet; 37, E. mongolica, lancet; 38, E. minuta, lancet; 39, E. loktini (holotype), lancet and lance." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/200962/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Fig. 
<number box="[1218,1250,894,918]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="36.0">36</number>
</figureCitation>
). Valviceps with a long basal lobe, forming very deep notch between valviceps and valvura (
<figureCitation box="[996,1080,930,954]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 58" captionStartId="30.[151,264,1927,1950]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[151,1436,193,1906]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 58. Penis valves of Empria longicornis group: 53, E. alpina; 54, E. mongolica; 55, E. loktini (paratype); 56, E. alector (specimen h- 32); 57, E. tridens (specimen 08 - 12); 58, E. minuta." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/200966/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Fig. 
<number box="[1049,1080,930,954]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="53.0">53</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,714,1028]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,225,967,991]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Notes.</emphasis>
Taxonomic identity is evident from the original description (e.g. fig 
<number box="[989,1002,967,990]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="7.0">7</number>
a in 
<bibRefCitation author="Benson" box="[1050,1207,966,990]" pageId="21" pageNumber="37" refString="Benson, R. B. (1938) A revision of the British sawflies of the genus Empria Lepeletier (Hymenoptera, Symphyta). Transactions of the Society of British Entomology, 5, 181 - 198." type="journal article" year="1938">
Benson, 
<number box="[1148,1207,966,990]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1938.0">1938</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), but confirmed also by studying three 
<typeStatus box="[352,459,1004,1028]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">paratypes</typeStatus>
(
<number box="[478,490,1003,1027]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1.0">1</number>
Ψ and 
<number box="[571,585,1003,1027]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1.0">1</number>
ɗ with same collecting data as 
<typeStatus box="[941,1044,1003,1027]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">holotype</typeStatus>
).
</paragraph>
